-GPIO function description:
(General Purpose I/Os)

-drivers required:
RCC driver

-BUS responsible for thi peripheral:
APB2

-Each of the general-purpose I/O ports has two 32-bit configuration registers (GPIOx_CRL, 
GPIOx_CRH), two 32-bit data registers (GPIOx_IDR, GPIOx_ODR), a 32-bit set/reset 
register (GPIOx_BSRR), a 16-bit reset register (GPIOx_BRR) and a 32-bit locking register 
(GPIOx_LCKR)

-configuration options for each pin:
 Input floating 
 Input pull-up
 Input-pull-down
 Analog
 Output open-drain
 Output push-pull
 Alternate function push-pull
 Alternate function open-drain


-driver functions description:
1) void GPIO_voidSetPinDirection(u8 Copy_u8PORT, u8 Copy_u8PIN, u8 Copy_u8Mode)
this function is responsible for setting the pin mode , either INPUT or OUTPUT with different options

2) void GPIO_voidSetPinValue(u8 Copy_u8PORT, u8 Copy_u8PIN, u8 Copy_u8Value)
function responsible for writing the pin value if this pin is output mode

3) u8 GPIO_voidGetPinValue(u8 Copy_u8PORT, u8 Copy_u8PIN)
function reads the pin value if this pin is input mode


